    "longBusinessSummary": "Vinh Hoan Corporation, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the farming and processing of frozen pangasius products in Vietnam and internationally. The company offers pangasius products, including portions, loins, fillets, strips, rolls, and cubes; marinated fish skewers and breaded fish products; fish powder and fins; shrimp chips; noodles and rice paper; drinking water; fully cooked and ready-to-eat fish products; and surimi products, such as fish tofu, crab chunk, crabsticks, and lucky bags, as well as barramundi, rolled shrimp, scallops, and salmon. It also provides freeze-dried fruits; and frozen fruits and vegetables, such as dragon fruit, mango, melon, and corn. In addition, the company offers collagen peptide used in nutraceuticals and cosmeceuticals; and gelatin used in confectionery, dairy, meat industry, desserts, soft capsules, and tablets. Further, it invests in companies for aquaculture and agriculture technology; provides livestock and aquatic feeds, oil and fat, and vegetable juice; trades in raw agricultural products and preprocessing materials, aquatic products and related husbandry products, chemicals, machines, equipment, and supplies; processing and preserving of aquatic products, fruits, and vegetables; and engages in fish hatchery and inland aquaculture activities. The company exports its products. Vinh Hoan Corporation was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Cao Lãnh, Vietnam.",
